nodes.bodyText:
So for example, we have a method getSpanNames, instead of iterating over running /completed spans, the processor can be something like
TracezSpanProcessor

private final Set<String> spanNames;

onStart(span) {
  spanNames.add(span.name);
}

onEnd(span) {
  spanNames.add(span.name);
}

And getSpanNames can just return that directly. From what I can tell, the information is mostly sets of names and counts, so I think we could do a similar approach for all of them (I didn't do a deep dive though so let me know if I missed something).
With the cap on the cache, things are still much safer, but if we keep track of the metrics themselves without storing spans, we wouldn't even need to worry about it, and I guess have better metrics? What do you think?

